reference "theorem: main"

\end_inset

 shows that many transfer sequences 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{ T_{t}\right\} _{t}$
\end_inset

 and asset profiles 
\begin_inset Formula $\left\{
b_{i,t},B_{t}\right\} _{i,t}$
\end_inset

 support the same equilibrium allocation. For example, one can set government assets 
\begin_inset Formula $B_{i,t}=0$
\end_inset

 without loss of generality. 
