\begin_layout Standard
We return to the more general problem formulated in section 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "Sec: environment"

\end_inset

. We further assume that 
\begin_inset Formula $U^{i}:\mathbb{R}_{+}^{2}\rightarrow \mathbb{R}$
\end_inset

 is concave in 
\begin_inset Formula $\left( c,-l\right) $
\end_inset

 and twice continuously differentiable. We let 
\begin_inset Formula $U_{x,t}^{i}\ $
\end_inset

or 
\begin_inset Formula $U_{xy,t}^{i}$
\end_inset

 denote first and second derivatives of 
\begin_inset Formula $U^{i}$
\end_inset

 with respect to 
\begin_inset Formula $x,y\in
\left\{ c,l\right\} $
\end_inset

 in period 
\begin_inset Formula $t$
\end_inset

 and assume that 
\begin_inset Formula $\lim_{x\rightarrow \bar{l}_{i}}U_{l}^{i}\left( c,x\right) =\infty $
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\lim_{x\rightarrow
0}U_{l}^{i}\left( c,x\right) =0$
\end_inset

 for all 
\begin_inset Formula $c$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $i.$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
We focus on interior equilibria. First-order necessary conditions for the consumer's problem are
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
\left( 1-\tau _{t}\right) \theta _{i,t}U_{c,t}^{i}=-U_{l,t}^{i},
\label{FOC consumption labor}
\end{equation}
\end_inset

and
\begin_inset Formula \begin{equation}
U_{c,t}^{i}=\beta\mathbb{E}_{t}R_{t+1}U_{c,t+1}^{i}.  \label{FOC Euler}
\end{equation}
\end_inset

To help characterize an equilibrium, we use
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\backslash
begin{proposition}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 
\begin_inset CommandInset label
LatexCommand label
name "prop: affine eqm nec and suff"

\end_inset

A sequence 
\begin_inset Formula $\{ \left \{
c_{i,t},l_{i,t},b_{i,t}\right \} _{i},R_{t},\tau _{t},T_{t}\}_t$
\end_inset

 is part of a competitive equilibrium with affine taxes if and only if it satisfies (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "feasibility goods"

\end_inset

), (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "agent bc affine"

\end_inset

), (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "FOC consumption labor"

\end_inset

), and (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "FOC Euler"

\end_inset

) and 
\begin_inset Formula $b_{i,t}$
\end_inset

 is bounded for all 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $t.$
\end_inset

 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\backslash
end{proposition}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\backslash
begin{proof}
\end_layout

\end_inset

 Necessity is obvious. In appendix 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "appndx: affine eqm nec and stuff"

\end_inset

, we use arguments of 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
after ""
before ""
key "Magill1994"

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset CommandInset citation
LatexCommand citet
after ""
before ""
key "Constantinides1996"

\end_inset

 to show that any 
\begin_inset Formula $\left \{
c_{i,t},l_{i,t},b_{i,t}\right \} _{i,t}$
\end_inset

 that satisfies (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "agent bc affine"

\end_inset

), (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "FOC consumption labor"

\end_inset

), and (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "FOC Euler"

\end_inset

) is a solution to consumer 
\begin_inset Formula $i$
\end_inset

's problem. Equilibrium 
\begin_inset Formula $\{B_{t}\}_t$
\end_inset

 is determined by (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "feasibility bonds"

\end_inset

) and constraint (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "govmt bc affine"

\end_inset

) is then implied by Walras' Law 
\begin_inset ERT
status collapsed

\begin_layout Plain Layout

\backslash
end{proof}
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
To find an optimal equilibrium, by Proposition 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "prop: affine eqm nec and suff"

\end_inset

 we can choose 
\begin_inset Formula $\{ \left \{ c_{i,t},l_{i,t},b_{i,t}\right \} _{i},R_{t},\tau
_{t},T_{t}\}_{t}$
\end_inset

 to maximize (
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "govmt objective"

\end_inset

) subject to (
